 140 class Line(object):
 141     def __init__(self, line, extras=None):
 142         # type: (AnyStr, Optional[Union[List[S], Set[S], Tuple[S, ...]]]) -> None
 143         self.editable = False  # type: bool
 144         if line.startswith("-e "):
 145             line = line[len("-e ") :]
 146             self.editable = True
 147         self.extras = ()  # type: Tuple[STRING_TYPE, ...]
 148         if extras is not None:
 149             self.extras = tuple(sorted(set(extras)))
 150         self.line = line  # type: STRING_TYPE
 151         self.hashes = []  # type: List[STRING_TYPE]
 152         self.markers = None  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 153         self.vcs = None  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 154         self.path = None  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 155         self.relpath = None  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 156         self.uri = None  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 157         self._link = None  # type: Optional[Link]
 158         self.is_local = False  # type: bool
 159         self._name = None  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 160         self._specifier = None  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 161         self.parsed_marker = None  # type: Optional[Marker]
 162         self.preferred_scheme = None  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 163         self._requirement = None  # type: Optional[PackagingRequirement]
 164         self._parsed_url = None  # type: Optional[URI]
 165         self._setup_cfg = None  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 166         self._setup_py = None  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 167         self._pyproject_toml = None  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 168         self._pyproject_requires = None  # type: Optional[Tuple[STRING_TYPE, ...]]
 169         self._pyproject_backend = None  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 170         self._wheel_kwargs = None  # type: Optional[Dict[STRING_TYPE, STRING_TYPE]]
 171         self._vcsrepo = None  # type: Optional[VCSRepository]
 172         self._setup_info = None  # type: Optional[SetupInfo]
 173         self._ref = None  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 174         self._ireq = None  # type: Optional[InstallRequirement]
 175         self._src_root = None  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 176         self.dist = None  # type: Any
 177         super(Line, self).__init__()
 178         self.parse()
 179 
 180     def __hash__(self):
 181         return hash(
 182             (
 183                 self.editable,
 184                 self.line,
 185                 self.markers,
 186                 tuple(self.extras),
 187                 tuple(self.hashes),
 188                 self.vcs,
 189                 self.uri,
 190                 self.path,
 191                 self.name,
 192                 self._requirement,
 193             )
 194         )
 195 
 196     def __repr__(self):
 197         try:
 198             return (
 199                 "<Line (editable={self.editable}, name={self._name}, path={self.path}, "
 200                 "uri={self.uri}, extras={self.extras}, markers={self.markers}, vcs={self.vcs}"
 201                 ", specifier={self._specifier}, pyproject={self._pyproject_toml}, "
 202                 "pyproject_requires={self._pyproject_requires}, "
 203                 "pyproject_backend={self._pyproject_backend}, ireq={self._ireq})>".format(
 204                     self=self
 205                 )
 206             )
 207         except Exception:
 208             return "<Line {0}>".format(self.__dict__.values())
 209 
 210     def __str__(self):
 211         # type: () -> str
 212         if self.markers:
 213             return "{0}; {1}".format(self.get_line(), self.markers)
 214         return self.get_line()
 215 
 216     def get_line(
 217         self, with_prefix=False, with_markers=False, with_hashes=True, as_list=False
 218     ):
 219         # type: (bool, bool, bool, bool) -> Union[STRING_TYPE, List[STRING_TYPE]]
 220         line = self.line
 221         extras_str = extras_to_string(self.extras)
 222         with_hashes = False if self.editable or self.is_vcs else with_hashes
 223         hash_list = ["--hash={0}".format(h) for h in self.hashes]
 224         if self.is_named:
 225             line = self.name_and_specifier
 226         elif self.is_direct_url:
 227             line = self.link.url
 228         elif extras_str:
 229             if self.is_vcs:
 230                 line = self.link.url
 231                 if "git+file:/" in line and "git+file:///" not in line:
 232                     line = line.replace("git+file:/", "git+file:///")
 233             elif extras_str not in line:
 234                 line = "{0}{1}".format(line, extras_str)
 235         # XXX: For using markers on vcs or url requirements, they can be used
 236         # as normal (i.e. no space between the requirement and the semicolon)
 237         # and no additional quoting as long as they are not editable requirements
 238         # HOWEVER, for editable requirements, the requirement+marker must be quoted
 239         # We do this here for the line-formatted versions, but leave it up to the
 240         # `Script.parse()` functionality in pipenv, for instance, to handle that
 241         # in a cross-platform manner for the `as_list` approach since that is how
 242         # we anticipate this will be used if passing directly to the command line
 243         # for pip.
 244         if with_markers and self.markers:
 245             line = "{0}; {1}".format(line, self.markers)
 246             if with_prefix and self.editable and not as_list:
 247                 line = '"{0}"'.format(line)
 248         if as_list:
 249             result_list = []
 250             if with_prefix and self.editable:
 251                 result_list.append("-e")
 252             result_list.append(line)
 253             if with_hashes:
 254                 result_list.extend(self.hashes)
 255             return result_list
 256         if with_prefix and self.editable:
 257             line = "-e {0}".format(line)
 258         if with_hashes and hash_list:
 259             line = "{0} {1}".format(line, " ".join(hash_list))
 260         return line
 261 
 262     @property
 263     def name_and_specifier(self):
 264         name_str, spec_str = "", ""
 265         if self.name:
 266             name_str = "{0}".format(self.name.lower())
 267             extras_str = extras_to_string(self.extras)
 268             if extras_str:
 269                 name_str = "{0}{1}".format(name_str, extras_str)
 270         if self.specifier:
 271             spec_str = "{0}".format(self.specifier)
 272         return "{0}{1}".format(name_str, spec_str)
 273 
 274     @classmethod
 275     def split_hashes(cls, line):
 276         # type: (S) -> Tuple[S, List[S]]
 277         if "--hash" not in line:
 278             return line, []
 279         split_line = line.split()
 280         line_parts = []  # type: List[S]
 281         hashes = []  # type: List[S]
 282         for part in split_line:
 283             if part.startswith("--hash"):
 284                 param, _, value = part.partition("=")
 285                 hashes.append(value)
 286             else:
 287                 line_parts.append(part)
 288         line = " ".join(line_parts)
 289         return line, hashes
 290 
 291     @property
 292     def line_with_prefix(self):
 293         # type: () -> STRING_TYPE
 294         return self.get_line(with_prefix=True, with_hashes=False)
 295 
 296     @property
 297     def line_for_ireq(self):
 298         # type: () -> STRING_TYPE
 299         line = ""  # type: STRING_TYPE
 300         if self.is_file or self.is_remote_url and not self.is_vcs:
 301             scheme = self.preferred_scheme if self.preferred_scheme is not None else "uri"
 302             local_line = next(
 303                 iter(
 304                     [
 305                         os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(f))
 306                         for f in [self.setup_py, self.setup_cfg, self.pyproject_toml]
 307                         if f is not None
 308                     ]
 309                 ),
 310                 None,
 311             )
 312             if local_line and self.extras:
 313                 local_line = "{0}{1}".format(local_line, extras_to_string(self.extras))
 314             line = local_line if local_line is not None else self.line
 315             if scheme == "path":
 316                 if not line and self.base_path is not None:
 317                     line = os.path.abspath(self.base_path)
 318             else:
 319                 if DIRECT_URL_RE.match(self.line):
 320                     uri = URI.parse(self.line)
 321                     line = uri.full_url
 322                     self._requirement = init_requirement(self.line)
 323                     line = convert_direct_url_to_url(self.line)
 324                 else:
 325                     if self.link:
 326                         line = self.link.url
 327                     else:
 328                         try:
 329                             uri = URI.parse(line)
 330                         except ValueError:
 331                             line = line
 332                         else:
 333                             line = uri.base_url
 334                             self._link = uri.as_link
 335 
 336         if self.editable:
 337             if not line:
 338                 if self.is_path or self.is_file:
 339                     if not self.path and self.url is not None:
 340                         line = pip_shims.shims.url_to_path(self.url)
 341                     else:
 342                         line = self.path
 343                     if self.extras:
 344                         line = "{0}{1}".format(line, extras_to_string(self.extras))
 345                 else:
 346                     line = self.link.url
 347         elif self.is_vcs and not self.editable:
 348             line = add_ssh_scheme_to_git_uri(self.line)
 349         if not line:
 350             line = self.line
 351         return line
 352 
 353     @property
 354     def base_path(self):
 355         # type: () -> Optional[S]
 356         if not self.link and not self.path:
 357             self.parse_link()
 358         if not self.path:
 359             pass
 360         path = normalize_path(self.path)
 361         if os.path.exists(path) and os.path.isdir(path):
 362             path = path
 363         elif os.path.exists(path) and os.path.isfile(path):
 364             path = os.path.dirname(path)
 365         else:
 366             path = None
 367         return path
 368 
 369     @property
 370     def setup_py(self):
 371         # type: () -> Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 372         if self._setup_py is None:
 373             self.populate_setup_paths()
 374         return self._setup_py
 375 
 376     @property

 378         # type: () -> Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 379         if self._setup_cfg is None:
 380             self.populate_setup_paths()
 381         return self._setup_cfg
 382 
 383     @property
 384     def pyproject_toml(self):
 385         # type: () -> Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 386         if self._pyproject_toml is None:
 387             self.populate_setup_paths()
 388         return self._pyproject_toml
 389 
 390     @property
 391     def specifier(self):
 392         # type: () -> Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 393         options = [self._specifier]
 394         for req in (self.ireq, self.requirement):
 395             if req is not None and getattr(req, "specifier", None):
 396                 options.append(req.specifier)
 397         specifier = next(
 398             iter(spec for spec in options if spec is not None), None
 399         )  # type: Optional[Union[Specifier, SpecifierSet]]
 400         spec_string = None  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 401         if specifier is not None:
 402             spec_string = specs_to_string(specifier)
 403         elif (
 404             specifier is None
 405             and not self.is_named
 406             and (self._setup_info is not None and self._setup_info.version)
 407         ):
 408             spec_string = "=={0}".format(self._setup_info.version)
 409         if spec_string:
 410             self._specifier = spec_string
 411         return self._specifier
 412 
 413     @specifier.setter
 414     def specifier(self, spec):
 415         # type: (str) -> None
 416         if not spec.startswith("=="):
 417             spec = "=={0}".format(spec)
 418         self._specifier = spec
 419         self.specifiers = SpecifierSet(spec)
 420 
 421     @property
 422     def specifiers(self):
 423         # type: () -> Optional[SpecifierSet]
 424         ireq_needs_specifier = False
 425         req_needs_specifier = False
 426         if self.ireq is None or self.ireq.req is None or not self.ireq.req.specifier:
 427             ireq_needs_specifier = True
 428         if self.requirement is None or not self.requirement.specifier:
 429             req_needs_specifier = True
 430         if any([ireq_needs_specifier, req_needs_specifier]):
 431             # TODO: Should we include versions for VCS dependencies? IS there a reason not
 432             # to? For now we are using hashes as the equivalent to pin
 433             # note: we need versions for direct dependencies at the very least
 434             if (
 435                 self.is_file
 436                 or self.is_remote_url
 437                 or self.is_path
 438                 or (self.is_vcs and not self.editable)
 439             ):
 440                 if self.specifier is not None:
 441                     specifier = self.specifier
 442                     if not isinstance(specifier, SpecifierSet):
 443                         specifier = SpecifierSet(specifier)
 444                     self.specifiers = specifier
 445                     return specifier
 446         if self.ireq is not None and self.ireq.req is not None:
 447             return self.ireq.req.specifier
 448         elif self.requirement is not None:
 449             return self.requirement.specifier
 450         return None
 451 
 452     @specifiers.setter
 453     def specifiers(self, specifiers):
 454         # type: (Union[Text, str, SpecifierSet]) -> None
 455         if not isinstance(specifiers, SpecifierSet):
 456             if isinstance(specifiers, six.string_types):
 457                 specifiers = SpecifierSet(specifiers)
 458             else:
 459                 raise TypeError("Must pass a string or a SpecifierSet")
 460         specs = self.get_requirement_specs(specifiers)
 461         if self.ireq is not None and self._ireq and self._ireq.req is not None:
 462             self._ireq.req.specifier = specifiers
 463             self._ireq.req.specs = specs
 464         if self.requirement is not None:
 465             self.requirement.specifier = specifiers
 466             self.requirement.specs = specs
 467 
 468     @classmethod
 469     def get_requirement_specs(cls, specifierset):
 470         # type: (SpecifierSet) -> List[Tuple[AnyStr, AnyStr]]
 471         specs = []
 472         spec = next(iter(specifierset._specs), None)
 473         if spec:
 474             specs.append(spec._spec)
 475         return specs
 476 
 477     @property
 478     def requirement(self):
 479         # type: () -> Optional[RequirementType]
 480         if self._requirement is None:
 481             self.parse_requirement()
 482             if self._requirement is None and self._name is not None:
 483                 self._requirement = init_requirement(canonicalize_name(self.name))
 484                 if self.is_file or self.is_remote_url and self._requirement is not None:
 485                     self._requirement.url = self.url
 486         if (
 487             self._requirement
 488             and self._requirement.specifier
 489             and not self._requirement.specs
 490         ):
 491             specs = self.get_requirement_specs(self._requirement.specifier)
 492             self._requirement.specs = specs
 493         return self._requirement
 494 
 495     def populate_setup_paths(self):
 496         # type: () -> None
 497         if not self.link and not self.path:
 498             self.parse_link()
 499         if not self.path:
 500             return
 501         base_path = self.base_path
 502         if base_path is None:
 503             return
 504         setup_paths = get_setup_paths(
 505             base_path, subdirectory=self.subdirectory
 506         )  # type: Dict[STRING_TYPE, Optional[STRING_TYPE]]
 507         self._setup_py = setup_paths.get("setup_py")
 508         self._setup_cfg = setup_paths.get("setup_cfg")
 509         self._pyproject_toml = setup_paths.get("pyproject_toml")
 510 
 511     @property
 512     def pyproject_requires(self):
 513         # type: () -> Optional[Tuple[STRING_TYPE, ...]]
 514         if self._pyproject_requires is None and self.pyproject_toml is not None:
 515             if self.path is not None:
 516                 pyproject_requires, pyproject_backend = None, None
 517                 pyproject_results = get_pyproject(self.path)  # type: ignore
 518                 if pyproject_results:
 519                     pyproject_requires, pyproject_backend = pyproject_results
 520                 if pyproject_requires:
 521                     self._pyproject_requires = tuple(pyproject_requires)
 522                 self._pyproject_backend = pyproject_backend
 523         return self._pyproject_requires
 524 
 525     @property
 526     def pyproject_backend(self):
 527         # type: () -> Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 528         if self._pyproject_requires is None and self.pyproject_toml is not None:
 529             pyproject_requires = None  # type: Optional[Sequence[STRING_TYPE]]
 530             pyproject_backend = None  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 531             pyproject_results = get_pyproject(self.path)  # type: ignore
 532             if pyproject_results:
 533                 pyproject_requires, pyproject_backend = pyproject_results
 534             if not pyproject_backend and self.setup_cfg is not None:
 535                 setup_dict = SetupInfo.get_setup_cfg(self.setup_cfg)
 536                 pyproject_backend = get_default_pyproject_backend()
 537                 pyproject_requires = setup_dict.get(
 538                     "build_requires", ["setuptools", "wheel"]
 539                 )  # type: ignore
 540             if pyproject_requires:
 541                 self._pyproject_requires = tuple(pyproject_requires)
 542             if pyproject_backend:
 543                 self._pyproject_backend = pyproject_backend
 544         return self._pyproject_backend
 545 
 546     def parse_hashes(self):
 547         # type: () -> "Line"
 548         """Parse hashes from *self.line* and set them on the current object.
 549 
 550         :returns: Self
 551         :rtype: `:class:~Line`
 552         """
 553         line, hashes = self.split_hashes(self.line)
 554         self.hashes = hashes
 555         self.line = line
 556         return self
 557 
 558     def parse_extras(self):
 559         # type: () -> "Line"
 560         """
 561         Parse extras from *self.line* and set them on the current object
 562         :returns: self
 563         :rtype: :class:`~Line`
 564         """
 565         extras = None
 566         line = "{0}".format(self.line)
 567         if any([self.is_vcs, self.is_url, "@" in line]):
 568             try:
 569                 if self.parsed_url.name:
 570                     self._name = self.parsed_url.name
 571                 if (
 572                     self.parsed_url.host
 573                     and self.parsed_url.path
 574                     and self.parsed_url.scheme
 575                 ):
 576                     self.line = self.parsed_url.to_string(
 577                         escape_password=False,
 578                         direct=False,
 579                         strip_ssh=self.parsed_url.is_implicit_ssh,
 580                     )
 581             except ValueError:
 582                 self.line, extras = pip_shims.shims._strip_extras(self.line)
 583         else:
 584             self.line, extras = pip_shims.shims._strip_extras(self.line)
 585         extras_set = set()  # type: Set[STRING_TYPE]
 586         if extras is not None:
 587             extras_set = set(parse_extras(extras))
 588         if self._name:
 589             self._name, name_extras = pip_shims.shims._strip_extras(self._name)
 590             if name_extras:
 591                 name_extras = set(parse_extras(name_extras))
 592                 extras_set |= name_extras
 593         if extras_set is not None:
 594             self.extras = tuple(sorted(extras_set))
 595         return self
 596 
 597     def get_url(self):
 598         # type: () -> STRING_TYPE
 599         """Sets ``self.name`` if given a **PEP-508** style URL."""
 600         return self.parsed_url.to_string(
 601             escape_password=False, direct=False, strip_ref=True
 602         )
 603 
 604     @property
 605     def name(self):
 606         # type: () -> Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 607         if self._name is None:
 608             self.parse_name()
 609             if self._name is None and not self.is_named and not self.is_wheel:
 610                 if self.setup_info:
 611                     self._name = self.setup_info.name
 612             elif self.is_wheel:
 613                 self._name = self._parse_wheel()
 614             if not self._name:
 615                 self._name = self.ireq.name
 616         return self._name
 617 
 618     @name.setter
 619     def name(self, name):
 620         # type: (STRING_TYPE) -> None
 621         self._name = name
 622         if self._setup_info:
 623             self._setup_info.name = name
 624         if self.requirement and self._requirement:
 625             self._requirement.name = name
 626         if self.ireq and self._ireq and self._ireq.req:
 627             self._ireq.req.name = name
 628 
 629     @property
 630     def url(self):
 631         # type: () -> Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 632         try:
 633             return self.parsed_url.to_string(
 634                 escape_password=False,
 635                 strip_ref=True,
 636                 strip_name=True,
 637                 strip_subdir=True,
 638                 strip_ssh=False,
 639             )
 640         except ValueError:
 641             return None
 642 
 643     @property
 644     def link(self):
 645         # type: () -> Link
 646         if self._link is None:
 647             self.parse_link()
 648         return self._link
 649 
 650     @property
 651     def subdirectory(self):
 652         # type: () -> Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 653         if self.link is not None:
 654             return self.link.subdirectory_fragment
 655         return ""
 656 
 657     @property
 658     def is_wheel(self):
 659         # type: () -> bool
 660         if self.link is None:
 661             return False
 662         return self.link.is_wheel
 663 
 664     @property
 665     def is_artifact(self):
 666         # type: () -> bool
 667 
 668         if self.link is None:
 669             return False
 670         return not self.link.is_vcs
 671 
 672     @property
 673     def is_vcs(self):
 674         # type: () -> bool
 675         # Installable local files and installable non-vcs urls are handled
 676         # as files, generally speaking
 677         try:
 678             if is_vcs(self.line) or is_vcs(self.get_url()):
 679                 return True
 680         except ValueError:
 681             return False
 682         return False
 683 
 684     @property
 685     def is_url(self):
 686         # type: () -> bool
 687         try:
 688             url = self.get_url()
 689         except ValueError:
 690             return False
 691         if is_valid_url(url) or is_file_url(url):
 692             return True
 693         return False
 694 
 695     @property
 696     def is_remote_url(self):
 697         # type: () -> bool
 698         return self.is_url and self.parsed_url.host is not None
 699 
 700     @property
 701     def is_path(self):
 702         # type: () -> bool
 703         try:
 704             line_url = self.get_url()
 705         except ValueError:
 706             line_url = None
 707         if (
 708             self.path
 709             and (
 710                 self.path.startswith(".")
 711                 or os.path.isabs(self.path)
 712                 or os.path.exists(self.path)
 713             )
 714             and is_installable_file(self.path)
 715         ):
 716             return True
 717         elif (os.path.exists(self.line) and is_installable_file(self.line)) or (
 718             line_url and os.path.exists(line_url) and is_installable_file(line_url)
 719         ):
 720             return True
 721         return False
 722 
 723     @property
 724     def is_file_url(self):
 725         # type: () -> bool
 726         try:
 727             url = self.get_url()
 728         except ValueError:
 729             return False
 730         try:
 731             parsed_url_scheme = self.parsed_url.scheme
 732         except ValueError:
 733             return False
 734         if url and is_file_url(url) or parsed_url_scheme == "file":
 735             return True
 736         return False
 737 
 738     @property
 739     def is_file(self):
 740         # type: () -> bool
 741         try:
 742             url = self.get_url()
 743         except ValueError:
 744             return False
 745         if (
 746             self.is_path
 747             or (is_file_url(url) and is_installable_file(url))
 748             or (
 749                 self._parsed_url
 750                 and self._parsed_url.is_file_url
 751                 and is_installable_file(self._parsed_url.url_without_fragment_or_ref)
 752             )
 753         ):
 754             return True
 755         return False
 756 
 757     @property
 758     def is_named(self):
 759         # type: () -> bool
 760         return not (
 761             self.is_file_url
 762             or self.is_url
 763             or self.is_file
 764             or self.is_vcs
 765             or self.is_direct_url
 766         )
 767 
 768     @property
 769     def ref(self):
 770         # type: () -> Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 771         if self._ref is None and self.relpath is not None:
 772             self.relpath, self._ref = split_ref_from_uri(self.relpath)
 773         return self._ref
 774 
 775     @property
 776     def ireq(self):
 777         # type: () -> Optional[pip_shims.InstallRequirement]
 778         if self._ireq is None:
 779             self.parse_ireq()
 780         return self._ireq
 781 
 782     @property
 783     def is_installable(self):
 784         # type: () -> bool
 785         try:
 786             url = self.get_url()
 787         except ValueError:
 788             url = None
 789         possible_paths = (self.line, url, self.path, self.base_path)
 790         return any(is_installable_file(p) for p in possible_paths if p is not None)
 791 
 792     @property
 793     def wheel_kwargs(self):
 794         if not self._wheel_kwargs:
 795             self._wheel_kwargs = _prepare_wheel_building_kwargs(self.ireq)
 796         return self._wheel_kwargs

 798     def get_setup_info(self):
 799         # type: () -> SetupInfo
 800         setup_info = None
 801         with pip_shims.shims.global_tempdir_manager():
 802             setup_info = SetupInfo.from_ireq(self.ireq, subdir=self.subdirectory)
 803             if not setup_info.name:
 804                 setup_info.get_info()
 805         return setup_info
 806 
 807     @property
 808     def setup_info(self):
 809         # type: () -> Optional[SetupInfo]
 810         if not self._setup_info and not self.is_named and not self.is_wheel:
 811             # make two attempts at this before failing to allow for stale data
 812             try:
 813                 self.setup_info = self.get_setup_info()
 814             except FileNotFoundError:
 815                 try:
 816                     self.setup_info = self.get_setup_info()
 817                 except FileNotFoundError:
 818                     raise
 819         return self._setup_info
 820 
 821     @setup_info.setter
 822     def setup_info(self, setup_info):
 823         # type: (SetupInfo) -> None
 824         self._setup_info = setup_info
 825         if setup_info.version:
 826             self.specifier = setup_info.version
 827         if setup_info.name and not self.name:
 828             self.name = setup_info.name

 830     def _get_vcsrepo(self):
 831         # type: () -> Optional[VCSRepository]
 832         from .vcs import VCSRepository
 833 
 834         checkout_directory = self.wheel_kwargs["src_dir"]  # type: ignore
 835         if self.name is not None:
 836             checkout_directory = os.path.join(
 837                 checkout_directory, self.name
 838             )  # type: ignore
 839         vcsrepo = VCSRepository(
 840             url=self.link.url,
 841             name=self.name,
 842             ref=self.ref if self.ref else None,
 843             checkout_directory=checkout_directory,
 844             vcs_type=self.vcs,
 845             subdirectory=self.subdirectory,
 846         )
 847         if not (self.link.scheme.startswith("file") and self.editable):
 848             vcsrepo.obtain()
 849         return vcsrepo
 850 
 851     @property
 852     def vcsrepo(self):
 853         # type: () -> Optional[VCSRepository]
 854         if self._vcsrepo is None and self.is_vcs:
 855             self._vcsrepo = self._get_vcsrepo()
 856         return self._vcsrepo

 858     @property
 859     def parsed_url(self):
 860         # type: () -> URI
 861         if self._parsed_url is None:
 862             self._parsed_url = URI.parse(self.line)
 863         return self._parsed_url
 864 
 865     @property
 866     def is_direct_url(self):
 867         # type: () -> bool
 868         try:
 869             return self.is_url and self.parsed_url.is_direct_url
 870         except ValueError:
 871             return self.is_url and bool(DIRECT_URL_RE.match(self.line))

 873     @cached_property
 874     def metadata(self):
 875         # type: () -> Dict[Any, Any]
 876         if self.is_local and self.path and is_installable_dir(self.path):
 877             return get_metadata(self.path)
 878         return {}
 879 
 880     @cached_property
 881     def parsed_setup_cfg(self):
 882         # type: () -> Dict[Any, Any]
 883         if not (
 884             self.is_local
 885             and self.path
 886             and is_installable_dir(self.path)
 887             and self.setup_cfg
 888         ):
 889             return {}
 890         return self.setup_info.parse_setup_cfg()
 891 
 892     @cached_property
 893     def parsed_setup_py(self):
 894         # type: () -> Dict[Any, Any]
 895         if self.is_local and self.path and is_installable_dir(self.path):
 896             if self.setup_py:
 897                 return ast_parse_setup_py(self.setup_py)
 898         return {}

 900     @vcsrepo.setter
 901     def vcsrepo(self, repo):
 902         # type (VCSRepository) -> None
 903         self._vcsrepo = repo
 904         ireq = self.ireq
 905         wheel_kwargs = self.wheel_kwargs.copy()
 906         wheel_kwargs["src_dir"] = repo.checkout_directory
 907         with pip_shims.shims.global_tempdir_manager(), temp_path():
 908             ireq.ensure_has_source_dir(wheel_kwargs["src_dir"])
 909             sys.path = [repo.checkout_directory, "", ".", get_python_lib(plat_specific=0)]
 910             setupinfo = SetupInfo.create(
 911                 repo.checkout_directory,
 912                 ireq=ireq,
 913                 subdirectory=self.subdirectory,
 914                 kwargs=wheel_kwargs,
 915             )
 916             self._setup_info = setupinfo
 917             self._setup_info.reload()
 918 
 919     def get_ireq(self):
 920         # type: () -> InstallRequirement
 921         line = self.line_for_ireq
 922         if self.editable:
 923             ireq = pip_shims.shims.install_req_from_editable(line)
 924         else:
 925             ireq = pip_shims.shims.install_req_from_line(line)
 926         if self.is_named:
 927             ireq = pip_shims.shims.install_req_from_line(self.line)
 928         if self.is_file or self.is_remote_url:
 929             ireq.link = self.link
 930         if self.extras and not ireq.extras:
 931             ireq.extras = set(self.extras)
 932         if self.parsed_marker is not None and not ireq.markers:
 933             ireq.markers = self.parsed_marker
 934         if not ireq.req and self._requirement is not None:
 935             ireq.req = copy.deepcopy(self._requirement)
 936         return ireq
 937 
 938     def parse_ireq(self):
 939         # type: () -> None
 940         if self._ireq is None:
 941             self._ireq = self.get_ireq()
 942         if self._ireq is not None:
 943             if self.requirement is not None and self._ireq.req is None:
 944                 self._ireq.req = self.requirement
 945 
 946     def _parse_wheel(self):
 947         # type: () -> Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 948         if not self.is_wheel:
 949             pass
 950         from pip_shims.shims import Wheel
 951 
 952         _wheel = Wheel(self.link.filename)
 953         name = _wheel.name
 954         version = _wheel.version
 955         self._specifier = "=={0}".format(version)
 956         return name
 957 
 958     def _parse_name_from_link(self):
 959         # type: () -> Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 960         if self.link is None:
 961             return None
 962         if getattr(self.link, "egg_fragment", None):
 963             return self.link.egg_fragment
 964         elif self.is_wheel:
 965             return self._parse_wheel()
 966         return None
 967 
 968     def _parse_name_from_line(self):
 969         # type: () -> Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 970         if not self.is_named:
 971             pass
 972         try:
 973             self._requirement = init_requirement(self.line)
 974         except Exception:
 975             raise RequirementError(
 976                 "Failed parsing requirement from {0!r}".format(self.line)
 977             )
 978         name = self._requirement.name
 979         if not self._specifier and self._requirement and self._requirement.specifier:
 980             self._specifier = specs_to_string(self._requirement.specifier)
 981         if self._requirement.extras and not self.extras:
 982             self.extras = self._requirement.extras
 983         if not name:
 984             name = self.line
 985             specifier_match = next(
 986                 iter(spec for spec in SPECIFIERS_BY_LENGTH if spec in self.line), None
 987             )
 988             specifier = None  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 989             if specifier_match:
 990                 specifier = "{0!s}".format(specifier_match)
 991             if specifier is not None and specifier in name:
 992                 version = None  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
 993                 name, specifier, version = name.partition(specifier)
 994                 self._specifier = "{0}{1}".format(specifier, version)
 995         return name
 996 
 997     def _parse_name_from_path(self):
 998         # type: () -> Optional[S]
 999         if self.path and self.is_local and is_installable_dir(self.path):
1000             metadata = get_metadata(self.path)
1001             if metadata:
1002                 name = metadata.get("name", "")
1003                 if name and name != "wheel":
1004                     return name
1005             parsed_setup_cfg = self.parsed_setup_cfg
1006             if parsed_setup_cfg:
1007                 name = parsed_setup_cfg.get("name", "")
1008                 if name:
1009                     return name
1010 
1011             parsed_setup_py = self.parsed_setup_py
1012             if parsed_setup_py:
1013                 name = parsed_setup_py.get("name", "")
1014                 if name and isinstance(name, six.string_types):
1015                     return name
1016         return None
1017 
1018     def parse_name(self):
1019         # type: () -> "Line"
1020         if self._name is None:
1021             name = None
1022             if self.link is not None and self.line_is_installable:
1023                 name = self._parse_name_from_link()
1024             if name is None and (
1025                 (self.is_remote_url or self.is_artifact or self.is_vcs)
1026                 and self._parsed_url
1027             ):
1028                 if self._parsed_url.fragment:
1029                     _, _, name = self._parsed_url.fragment.partition("egg=")
1030                     if "&" in name:
1031                         # subdirectory fragments might also be in here
1032                         name, _, _ = name.partition("&")
1033             if name is None and self.is_named:
1034                 name = self._parse_name_from_line()
1035             elif name is None and self.is_file or self.is_remote_url or self.is_path:
1036                 if self.is_local:
1037                     name = self._parse_name_from_path()
1038             if name is not None:
1039                 name, extras = pip_shims.shims._strip_extras(name)
1040                 if extras is not None and not self.extras:
1041                     self.extras = tuple(sorted(set(parse_extras(extras))))
1042                 self._name = name
1043         return self
1044 
1045     def _parse_requirement_from_vcs(self):
1046         # type: () -> Optional[PackagingRequirement]
1047         url = self.url if self.url else self.link.url
1048         if url:
1049             url = unquote(url)
1050         if (
1051             url
1052             and self.uri != url
1053             and "git+ssh://" in url
1054             and (self.uri is not None and "git+git@" in self.uri)
1055             and self._requirement is not None
1056         ):
1057             self._requirement.line = self.uri
1058             self._requirement.url = self.url
1059             vcs_uri = build_vcs_uri(  # type: ignore
1060                 vcs=self.vcs,
1061                 uri=self.url,
1062                 ref=self.ref,
1063                 subdirectory=self.subdirectory,
1064                 extras=self.extras,
1065                 name=self.name,
1066             )
1067             if vcs_uri:
1068                 self._requirement.link = create_link(vcs_uri)
1069             elif self.link:
1070                 self._requirement.link = self.link
1071         # else:
1072         #     req.link = self.link
1073         if self.ref and self._requirement is not None:
1074             self._requirement.revision = self.ref
1075             if self._vcsrepo is not None:
1076                 with pip_shims.shims.global_tempdir_manager():
1077                     self._requirement.revision = self._vcsrepo.get_commit_hash()
1078         return self._requirement
1079 
1080     def parse_requirement(self):
1081         # type: () -> "Line"
1082         if self._name is None:
1083             self.parse_name()
1084             if not any([self._name, self.is_vcs, self.is_named]):
1085                 if self.setup_info and self.setup_info.name:
1086                     self._name = self.setup_info.name
1087         name, extras, url = self.requirement_info
1088         if name:
1089             self._requirement = init_requirement(name)  # type: PackagingRequirement
1090             if extras:
1091                 self._requirement.extras = set(extras)
1092             if url:
1093                 self._requirement.url = url
1094             if self.is_direct_url:
1095                 url = self.link.url
1096             if self.link:
1097                 self._requirement.link = self.link
1098             self._requirement.editable = self.editable
1099             if self.path and self.link and self.link.scheme.startswith("file"):
1100                 self._requirement.local_file = True
1101                 self._requirement.path = self.path
1102             if self.is_vcs:
1103                 self._requirement.vcs = self.vcs
1104                 self._requirement.line = self.link.url
1105                 self._parse_requirement_from_vcs()
1106             else:
1107                 self._requirement.line = self.line
1108             if self.parsed_marker is not None:
1109                 self._requirement.marker = self.parsed_marker
1110             if self.specifiers:
1111                 self._requirement.specifier = self.specifiers
1112                 specs = []
1113                 spec = next(iter(s for s in self.specifiers._specs), None)
1114                 if spec:
1115                     specs.append(spec._spec)
1116                 self._requirement.spec = spec
1117         else:
1118             if self.is_vcs:
1119                 raise ValueError(
1120                     "pipenv requires an #egg fragment for version controlled "
1121                     "dependencies. Please install remote dependency "
1122                     "in the form {0}#egg=<package-name>.".format(url)
1123                 )
1124         return self
1125 
1126     def parse_link(self):
1127         # type: () -> "Line"
1128         parsed_url = None  # type: Optional[URI]
1129         if (
1130             not is_valid_url(self.line)
1131             and is_installable_file(os.path.abspath(self.line))
1132             and (
1133                 self.line.startswith("./")
1134                 or (os.path.exists(self.line) or os.path.isabs(self.line))
1135             )
1136         ):
1137             url = pip_shims.shims.path_to_url(os.path.abspath(self.line))
1138             self._parsed_url = parsed_url = URI.parse(url)
1139         elif any(
1140             [
1141                 is_valid_url(self.line),
1142                 is_vcs(self.line),
1143                 is_file_url(self.line),
1144                 self.is_direct_url,
1145             ]
1146         ):
1147             parsed_url = self.parsed_url
1148         if parsed_url is None or (
1149             parsed_url.is_file_url and not parsed_url.is_installable
1150         ):
1151             return None
1152         if parsed_url.is_vcs:
1153             self.vcs, _ = parsed_url.scheme.split("+")
1154         if parsed_url.is_file_url:
1155             self.is_local = True
1156         parsed_link = parsed_url.as_link
1157         self._ref = parsed_url.ref
1158         self.uri = parsed_url.bare_url
1159         if parsed_url.name:
1160             self._name = parsed_url.name
1161         if parsed_url.extras:
1162             self.extras = tuple(sorted(set(parsed_url.extras)))
1163         self._link = parsed_link
1164         vcs, prefer, relpath, path, uri, link = FileRequirement.get_link_from_line(
1165             self.line
1166         )
1167         ref = None
1168         if link is not None and "@" in unquote(link.path) and uri is not None:
1169             uri, _, ref = unquote(uri).rpartition("@")
1170         if relpath is not None and "@" in relpath:
1171             relpath, _, ref = relpath.rpartition("@")
1172         if path is not None and "@" in path:
1173             path, _ = split_ref_from_uri(path)
1174         link_url = link.url_without_fragment
1175         if "@" in link_url:
1176             link_url, _ = split_ref_from_uri(link_url)
1177         self.preferred_scheme = prefer
1178         self.relpath = relpath
1179         self.path = path
1180         # self.uri = uri
1181         if prefer in ("path", "relpath") or uri.startswith("file"):
1182             self.is_local = True
1183         if parsed_url.is_vcs or parsed_url.is_direct_url and parsed_link:
1184             self._link = parsed_link
1185         else:
1186             self._link = link
1187         return self
1188 
1189     def parse_markers(self):
1190         # type: () -> None
1191         if self.markers:
1192             marker_str = self.markers.replace('"', "'")
1193             markers = PackagingRequirement("fakepkg; {0}".format(marker_str)).marker
1194             self.parsed_marker = markers
1195 
1196     @property
1197     def requirement_info(self):
1198         # type: () -> Tuple[Optional[S], Tuple[Optional[S], ...], Optional[S]]
1199         """
1200         Generates a 3-tuple of the requisite *name*, *extras* and *url* to generate a
1201         :class:`~packaging.requirements.Requirement` out of.
1202 
1203         :return: A Tuple of an optional name, a Tuple of extras, and an optional URL.
1204         :rtype: Tuple[Optional[S], Tuple[Optional[S], ...], Optional[S]]
1205         """
1206 
1207         # Direct URLs can be converted to packaging requirements directly, but
1208         # only if they are `file://` (with only two slashes)
1209         name = None  # type: Optional[S]
1210         extras = ()  # type: Tuple[Optional[S], ...]
1211         url = None  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
1212         # if self.is_direct_url:
1213         if self._name:
1214             name = canonicalize_name(self._name)
1215         if self.is_file or self.is_url or self.is_path or self.is_file_url or self.is_vcs:
1216             url = ""
1217             if self.is_vcs:
1218                 url = self.url if self.url else self.uri
1219                 if self.is_direct_url:
1220                     url = self.link.url_without_fragment
1221             else:
1222                 if self.link:
1223                     url = self.link.url_without_fragment
1224                 elif self.url:
1225                     url = self.url
1226                     if self.ref:
1227                         url = "{0}@{1}".format(url, self.ref)
1228                 else:
1229                     url = self.uri
1230             if self.link and name is None:
1231                 self._name = self.link.egg_fragment
1232                 if self._name:
1233                     name = canonicalize_name(self._name)
1234         return name, extras, url  # type: ignore
1235 
1236     @property
1237     def line_is_installable(self):
1238         # type: () -> bool
1239         """This is a safeguard against decoy requirements when a user installs
1240         a package whose name coincides with the name of a folder in the cwd,
1241         e.g. install *alembic* when there is a folder called *alembic* in the
1242         working directory.
1243 
1244         In this case we first need to check that the given requirement
1245         is a valid URL, VCS requirement, or installable filesystem path
1246         before deciding to treat it as a file requirement over a named
1247         requirement.
1248         """
1249         line = self.line
1250         direct_url_match = DIRECT_URL_RE.match(line)
1251         if direct_url_match:
1252             match_dict = direct_url_match.groupdict()
1253             auth = ""
1254             username = match_dict.get("username", None)
1255             password = match_dict.get("password", None)
1256             port = match_dict.get("port", None)
1257             path = match_dict.get("path", None)
1258             ref = match_dict.get("ref", None)
1259             if username is not None:
1260                 auth = "{0}".format(username)
1261             if password:
1262                 auth = "{0}:{1}".format(auth, password) if auth else password
1263             line = match_dict.get("host", "")
1264             if auth:
1265                 line = "{auth}@{line}".format(auth=auth, line=line)
1266             if port:
1267                 line = "{line}:{port}".format(line=line, port=port)
1268             if path:
1269                 line = "{line}{pathsep}{path}".format(
1270                     line=line, pathsep=match_dict["pathsep"], path=path
1271                 )
1272             if ref:
1273                 line = "{line}@{ref}".format(line=line, ref=ref)
1274             line = "{scheme}{line}".format(scheme=match_dict["scheme"], line=line)
1275         if is_file_url(line):
1276             link = create_link(line)
1277             line = link.url_without_fragment
1278             line, _ = split_ref_from_uri(line)
1279         if (
1280             is_vcs(line)
1281             or (not is_file_url(line) and is_valid_url(line))
1282             or (is_file_url(line) and is_installable_file(line))
1283             or is_installable_file(line)
1284         ):
1285             return True
1286         return False
1287 
1288     def parse(self):
1289         # type: () -> None
1290         self.line = self.line.strip()
1291         if self.line.startswith('"'):
1292             self.line = self.line.strip('"')
1293         self.line, self.markers = split_markers_from_line(self.parse_hashes().line)
1294         if self.markers:
1295             self.markers = self.markers.replace('"', "'")
1296         self.parse_extras()
1297         self.line = self.line.strip('"').strip("'").strip()
1298         if self.line.startswith("git+file:/") and not self.line.startswith(
1299             "git+file:///"
1300         ):
1301             self.line = self.line.replace("git+file:/", "git+file:///")
1302         self.parse_markers()
1303         if self.is_file_url:
1304             if self.line_is_installable:
1305                 self.populate_setup_paths()
1306             else:
1307                 raise RequirementError(
1308                     "Supplied requirement is not installable: {0!r}".format(self.line)
1309                 )
1310         elif self.is_named and self._name is None:
1311             self.parse_name()
1312         self.parse_link()
1313         # self.parse_requirement()
1314         # self.parse_ireq()
1315

1317 @attr.s(slots=True, hash=True)
1318 class NamedRequirement(object):
1319     name = attr.ib()  # type: STRING_TYPE

1321     req = attr.ib()  # type: PackagingRequirement
1322     extras = attr.ib(default=attr.Factory(list))  # type: Tuple[STRING_TYPE, ...]
1323     editable = attr.ib(default=False)  # type: bool
1324     _parsed_line = attr.ib(default=None)  # type: Optional[Line]

1326     @req.default
1327     def get_requirement(self):
1328         # type: () -> RequirementType
1329         req = init_requirement(
1330             "{0}{1}".format(canonicalize_name(self.name), self.version)

1334     @property
1335     def parsed_line(self):

1341     @classmethod
1342     def from_line(cls, line, parsed_line=None):
1343         # type: (AnyStr, Optional[Line]) -> NamedRequirement
1344         req = init_requirement(line)
1345         specifiers = None  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
1346         if req.specifier:
1347             specifiers = specs_to_string(req.specifier)
1348         req.line = line
1349         name = getattr(req, "name", None)
1350         if not name:
1351             name = getattr(req, "project_name", None)
1352             req.name = name
1353         if not name:
1354             name = getattr(req, "key", line)
1355             req.name = name
1356         creation_kwargs = {
1357             "name": name,
1358             "version": specifiers,
1359             "req": req,
1360             "parsed_line": parsed_line,
1361             "extras": None,
1362         }
1363         extras = None  # type: Optional[Tuple[STRING_TYPE, ...]]
1364         if req.extras:
1365             extras = tuple(req.extras)
1366         creation_kwargs["extras"] = extras
1367         return cls(**creation_kwargs)
1368 
1369     @classmethod
1370     def from_pipfile(cls, name, pipfile):
1371         # type: (S, TPIPFILE) -> NamedRequirement
1372         creation_args = {}  # type: TPIPFILE
1373         if hasattr(pipfile, "keys"):
1374             attr_fields = [field.name for field in attr.fields(cls)]
1375             creation_args = {
1376                 k: v for k, v in pipfile.items() if k in attr_fields
1377             }  # type: ignore
1378         creation_args["name"] = name
1379         version = get_version(pipfile)  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
1380         extras = creation_args.get("extras", None)
1381         creation_args["version"] = version  # type: ignore
1382         req = init_requirement("{0}{1}".format(name, version))
1383         if req and extras and req.extras and isinstance(req.extras, tuple):
1384             if isinstance(extras, six.string_types):
1385                 req.extras = (extras) + tuple(["{0}".format(xtra) for xtra in req.extras])
1386             elif isinstance(extras, (tuple, list)):
1387                 req.extras += tuple(extras)
1388         creation_args["req"] = req
1389         return cls(**creation_args)  # type: ignore

1391     @property
1392     def line_part(self):
1393         # type: () -> STRING_TYPE
1394         # FIXME: This should actually be canonicalized but for now we have to
1395         # simply lowercase it and replace underscores, since full canonicalization
1396         # also replaces dots and that doesn't actually work when querying the index
1397         return normalize_name(self.name)

1399     @property
1400     def pipfile_part(self):
1401         # type: () -> Dict[STRING_TYPE, Any]
1402         pipfile_dict = attr.asdict(self, filter=filter_none).copy()  # type: ignore
1403         if "version" not in pipfile_dict:
1404             pipfile_dict["version"] = "*"
1405         if "_parsed_line" in pipfile_dict:
1406             pipfile_dict.pop("_parsed_line")
1407         name = pipfile_dict.pop("name")
1408         return {name: pipfile_dict}

1454     @classmethod
1455     def get_link_from_line(cls, line):
1456         # type: (STRING_TYPE) -> LinkInfo
1457         """Parse link information from given requirement line.
1458 
1459         Return a 6-tuple:
1460 
1461         - `vcs_type` indicates the VCS to use (e.g. "git"), or None.
1462         - `prefer` is either "file", "path" or "uri", indicating how the
1463             information should be used in later stages.
1464         - `relpath` is the relative path to use when recording the dependency,
1465             instead of the absolute path/URI used to perform installation.
1466             This can be None (to prefer the absolute path or URI).
1467         - `path` is the absolute file path to the package. This will always use
1468             forward slashes. Can be None if the line is a remote URI.
1469         - `uri` is the absolute URI to the package. Can be None if the line is
1470             not a URI.
1471         - `link` is an instance of :class:`pip._internal.index.Link`,
1472             representing a URI parse result based on the value of `uri`.
1473 
1474         This function is provided to deal with edge cases concerning URIs
1475         without a valid netloc. Those URIs are problematic to a straight
1476         ``urlsplit` call because they cannot be reliably reconstructed with
1477         ``urlunsplit`` due to a bug in the standard library:
1478 
1479         >>> from urllib.parse import urlsplit, urlunsplit
1480         >>> urlunsplit(urlsplit('git+file:///this/breaks'))
1481         'git+file:/this/breaks'
1482         >>> urlunsplit(urlsplit('file:///this/works'))
1483         'file:///this/works'
1484 
1485         See `https://bugs.python.org/issue23505#msg277350`.
1486         """
1487 
1488         # Git allows `git@github.com...` lines that are not really URIs.
1489         # Add "ssh://" so we can parse correctly, and restore afterwards.
1490         fixed_line = add_ssh_scheme_to_git_uri(line)  # type: STRING_TYPE
1491         added_ssh_scheme = fixed_line != line  # type: bool
1492 
1493         # We can assume a lot of things if this is a local filesystem path.
1494         if "://" not in fixed_line:
1495             p = Path(fixed_line).absolute()  # type: Path
1496             path = p.as_posix()  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
1497             uri = p.as_uri()  # type: STRING_TYPE
1498             link = create_link(uri)  # type: Link
1499             relpath = None  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
1500             try:
1501                 relpath = get_converted_relative_path(path)
1502             except ValueError:
1503                 relpath = None
1504             return LinkInfo(None, "path", relpath, path, uri, link)
1505 
1506         # This is an URI. We'll need to perform some elaborated parsing.
1507 
1508         parsed_url = urllib_parse.urlsplit(fixed_line)  # type: SplitResult
1509         original_url = parsed_url._replace()  # type: SplitResult
1510 
1511         # Split the VCS part out if needed.
1512         original_scheme = parsed_url.scheme  # type: STRING_TYPE
1513         vcs_type = None  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
1514         if "+" in original_scheme:
1515             scheme = None  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
1516             vcs_type, _, scheme = original_scheme.partition("+")
1517             parsed_url = parsed_url._replace(scheme=scheme)  # type: ignore
1518             prefer = "uri"  # type: STRING_TYPE
1519         else:
1520             vcs_type = None
1521             prefer = "file"
1522 
1523         if parsed_url.scheme == "file" and parsed_url.path:
1524             # This is a "file://" URI. Use url_to_path and path_to_url to
1525             # ensure the path is absolute. Also we need to build relpath.
1526             path = Path(
1527                 pip_shims.shims.url_to_path(urllib_parse.urlunsplit(parsed_url))
1528             ).as_posix()
1529             try:
1530                 relpath = get_converted_relative_path(path)
1531             except ValueError:
1532                 relpath = None
1533             uri = pip_shims.shims.path_to_url(path)
1534         else:
1535             # This is a remote URI. Simply use it.
1536             path = None
1537             relpath = None
1538             # Cut the fragment, but otherwise this is fixed_line.
1539             uri = urllib_parse.urlunsplit(
1540                 parsed_url._replace(scheme=original_scheme, fragment="")  # type: ignore
1541             )
1542 
1543         if added_ssh_scheme:
1544             original_uri = urllib_parse.urlunsplit(
1545                 original_url._replace(scheme=original_scheme, fragment="")  # type: ignore
1546             )
1547             uri = strip_ssh_from_git_uri(original_uri)
1548 
1549         # Re-attach VCS prefix to build a Link.
1550         link = create_link(
1551             urllib_parse.urlunsplit(
1552                 parsed_url._replace(scheme=original_scheme)
1553             )  # type: ignore
1554         )
1555 
1556         return LinkInfo(vcs_type, prefer, relpath, path, uri, link)
1557 
1558     @property
1559     def setup_py_dir(self):

1565     @property
1566     def dependencies(self):
1567         # type: () -> Tuple[Dict[S, PackagingRequirement], List[Union[S, PackagingRequirement]], List[S]]
1568         build_deps = []  # type: List[Union[S, PackagingRequirement]]
1569         setup_deps = []  # type: List[S]
1570         deps = {}  # type: Dict[S, PackagingRequirement]
1571         if self.setup_info:
1572             setup_info = self.setup_info.as_dict()
1573             deps.update(setup_info.get("requires", {}))
1574             setup_deps.extend(setup_info.get("setup_requires", []))
1575             build_deps.extend(setup_info.get("build_requires", []))
1576             if self.extras and self.setup_info.extras:
1577                 for dep in self.extras:
1578                     if dep not in self.setup_info.extras:
1579                         continue
1580                     extras_list = self.setup_info.extras.get(dep, [])  # type: ignore
1581                     for req_instance in extras_list:  # type: ignore
1582                         deps[req_instance.key] = req_instance
1583         if self.pyproject_requires:
1584             build_deps.extend(list(self.pyproject_requires))
1585         setup_deps = list(set(setup_deps))
1586         build_deps = list(set(build_deps))
1587         return deps, setup_deps, build_deps

1597             self._parsed_line is not None and self._parsed_line.requirement is not None

1600         if (
1601             self._parsed_line
1602             and self._parsed_line.ireq
1603             and not self._parsed_line.ireq.req

1641     @uri.default

1646             return pip_shims.shims.path_to_url(os.path.abspath(self.path))
1647         elif (
1648             getattr(self, "req", None)
1649             and self.req is not None
1650             and getattr(self.req, "url")

1653         elif self.link is not None:

1667     @link.default

1670         target = "{0}".format(self.uri)
1671         if hasattr(self, "name") and not self._has_hashed_name:
1672             target = "{0}#egg={1}".format(target, self.name)

1676     @req.default
1677     def get_requirement(self):
1678         # type: () -> RequirementType
1679         if self.name is None:
1680             if self._parsed_line is not None and self._parsed_line.name is not None:
1681                 self.name = self._parsed_line.name
1682             else:
1683                 raise ValueError(
1684                     "Failed to generate a requirement: missing name for {0!r}".format(
1685                         self
1686                     )
1687                 )
1688         if self._parsed_line:
1689             try:
1690                 # initialize specifiers to make sure we capture them
1691                 self._parsed_line.specifiers
1692             except Exception:
1693                 pass
1694             req = copy.deepcopy(self._parsed_line.requirement)
1695             if req:
1696                 return req

1698     @property
1699     def parsed_line(self):
1700         # type: () -> Optional[Line]
1701         if self._parsed_line is None:
1702             self._parsed_line = Line(self.line_part)
1703         return self._parsed_line

1705     @property
1706     def is_local(self):
1707         # type: () -> bool
1708         uri = getattr(self, "uri", None)
1709         if uri is None:
1710             if getattr(self, "path", None) and self.path is not None:
1711                 uri = pip_shims.shims.path_to_url(os.path.abspath(self.path))
1712             elif (
1713                 getattr(self, "req", None)
1714                 and self.req is not None
1715                 and (getattr(self.req, "url") and self.req.url is not None)
1716             ):
1717                 uri = self.req.url
1718             if uri and is_file_url(uri):
1719                 return True
1720         return False
1721 
1722     @property

1724         # type: () -> bool
1725         if self.link is None:
1726             return False
1727         return (
1728             self._parsed_line
1729             and not self._parsed_line.is_local
1730             and (self._parsed_line.is_artifact or self._parsed_line.is_wheel)
1731             and not self.editable
1732         )

1741     @property

1745             path = self.path
1746             if not isinstance(path, Path):

1757     @classmethod
1758     def from_pipfile(cls, name, pipfile):
1759         # type: (STRING_TYPE, Dict[STRING_TYPE, Union[Tuple[STRING_TYPE, ...], STRING_TYPE, bool]]) -> F
1760         # Parse the values out. After this dance we should have two variables:
1761         # path - Local filesystem path.
1762         # uri - Absolute URI that is parsable with urlsplit.
1763         # One of these will be a string; the other would be None.
1764         uri = pipfile.get("uri")
1765         fil = pipfile.get("file")
1766         path = pipfile.get("path")
1767         if path and isinstance(path, six.string_types):
1768             if isinstance(path, Path) and not path.is_absolute():
1769                 path = get_converted_relative_path(path.as_posix())
1770             elif not os.path.isabs(path):
1771                 path = get_converted_relative_path(path)
1772         if path and uri:
1773             raise ValueError("do not specify both 'path' and 'uri'")
1774         if path and fil:
1775             raise ValueError("do not specify both 'path' and 'file'")
1776         uri = uri or fil
1777 
1778         # Decide that scheme to use.
1779         # 'path' - local filesystem path.
1780         # 'file' - A file:// URI (possibly with VCS prefix).
1781         # 'uri' - Any other URI.
1782         if path:
1783             uri_scheme = "path"
1784         else:
1785             # URI is not currently a valid key in pipfile entries
1786             # see https://github.com/pypa/pipfile/issues/110
1787             uri_scheme = "file"
1788 
1789         if not uri:
1790             uri = pip_shims.shims.path_to_url(path)
1791         link_info = None  # type: Optional[LinkInfo]
1792         if uri and isinstance(uri, six.string_types):
1793             link_info = cls.get_link_from_line(uri)
1794         else:
1795             raise ValueError(
1796                 "Failed parsing requirement from pipfile: {0!r}".format(pipfile)
1797             )
1798         link = None  # type: Optional[Link]
1799         if link_info:
1800             link = link_info.link
1801             if link.url_without_fragment:
1802                 uri = unquote(link.url_without_fragment)
1803         extras = ()  # type: Optional[Tuple[STRING_TYPE, ...]]
1804         if "extras" in pipfile:
1805             extras = tuple(pipfile["extras"])  # type: ignore
1806         editable = pipfile["editable"] if "editable" in pipfile else False
1807         arg_dict = {
1808             "name": name,
1809             "path": path,
1810             "uri": uri,
1811             "editable": editable,
1812             "link": link,
1813             "uri_scheme": uri_scheme,
1814             "extras": extras if extras else None,
1815         }
1816 
1817         line = ""  # type: STRING_TYPE
1818         extras_string = "" if not extras else extras_to_string(extras)
1819         if editable and uri_scheme == "path":
1820             line = "{0}{1}".format(path, extras_string)
1821         else:
1822             if name:
1823                 line_name = "{0}{1}".format(name, extras_string)
1824                 line = "{0}#egg={1}".format(unquote(link.url_without_fragment), line_name)
1825             else:
1826                 if link:
1827                     line = unquote(link.url)
1828                 elif uri and isinstance(uri, six.string_types):
1829                     line = uri
1830                 else:
1831                     raise ValueError(
1832                         "Failed parsing requirement from pipfile: {0!r}".format(pipfile)
1833                     )
1834                 line = "{0}{1}".format(line, extras_string)
1835             if "subdirectory" in pipfile:
1836                 arg_dict["subdirectory"] = pipfile["subdirectory"]
1837                 line = "{0}&subdirectory={1}".format(line, pipfile["subdirectory"])
1838         if editable:
1839             line = "-e {0}".format(line)
1840         arg_dict["parsed_line"] = Line(line)
1841         arg_dict["setup_info"] = arg_dict["parsed_line"].setup_info
1842         return cls(**arg_dict)  # type: ignore
1843 
1844     @property
1845     def line_part(self):
1846         # type: () -> STRING_TYPE
1847         link_url = None  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
1848         seed = None  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
1849         if self.link is not None:
1850             link_url = unquote(self.link.url_without_fragment)
1851         is_vcs = getattr(self.link, "is_vcs", not self.link.is_artifact)
1852         if self._uri_scheme and self._uri_scheme == "path":
1853             # We may need any one of these for passing to pip
1854             seed = self.path or link_url or self.uri
1855         elif (self._uri_scheme and self._uri_scheme == "file") or (
1856             (self.link.is_wheel or not is_vcs) and self.link.url
1857         ):
1858             seed = link_url or self.uri
1859         # add egg fragments to remote artifacts (valid urls only)
1860         if not self._has_hashed_name and self.is_remote_artifact and seed is not None:
1861             seed += "#egg={0}".format(self.name)
1862         editable = "-e " if self.editable else ""
1863         if seed is None:
1864             raise ValueError("Could not calculate url for {0!r}".format(self))
1865         return "{0}{1}".format(editable, seed)
1866 
1867     @property
1868     def pipfile_part(self):
1869         # type: () -> Dict[AnyStr, Dict[AnyStr, Any]]
1870         excludes = [
1871             "_base_line",
1872             "_has_hashed_name",
1873             "setup_path",
1874             "pyproject_path",
1875             "_uri_scheme",
1876             "pyproject_requires",
1877             "pyproject_backend",
1878             "_setup_info",
1879             "_parsed_line",
1880         ]
1881         filter_func = lambda k, v: bool(v) is True and k.name not in excludes  # noqa
1882         pipfile_dict = attr.asdict(self, filter=filter_func).copy()  # type: Dict
1883         name = pipfile_dict.pop("name", None)
1884         if name is None:
1885             if self.name:
1886                 name = self.name
1887             elif self.parsed_line and self.parsed_line.name:
1888                 name = self.name = self.parsed_line.name
1889             elif self.setup_info and self.setup_info.name:
1890                 name = self.name = self.setup_info.name
1891         if "_uri_scheme" in pipfile_dict:
1892             pipfile_dict.pop("_uri_scheme")
1893         # For local paths and remote installable artifacts (zipfiles, etc)
1894         collision_keys = {"file", "uri", "path"}
1895         collision_order = ["file", "uri", "path"]  # type: List[STRING_TYPE]
1896         collisions = []  # type: List[STRING_TYPE]
1897         key_match = next(iter(k for k in collision_order if k in pipfile_dict.keys()))
1898         is_vcs = None
1899         if self.link is not None:
1900             is_vcs = getattr(self.link, "is_vcs", not self.link.is_artifact)
1901         if self._uri_scheme:
1902             dict_key = self._uri_scheme
1903             target_key = dict_key if dict_key in pipfile_dict else key_match
1904             if target_key is not None:
1905                 winning_value = pipfile_dict.pop(target_key)
1906                 collisions = [k for k in collision_keys if k in pipfile_dict]
1907                 for key in collisions:
1908                     pipfile_dict.pop(key)
1909                 pipfile_dict[dict_key] = winning_value
1910         elif (
1911             self.is_remote_artifact
1912             or (is_vcs is not None and not is_vcs)
1913             and (self._uri_scheme and self._uri_scheme == "file")
1914         ):
1915             dict_key = "file"
1916             # Look for uri first because file is a uri format and this is designed
1917             # to make sure we add file keys to the pipfile as a replacement of uri
1918             if key_match is not None:
1919                 winning_value = pipfile_dict.pop(key_match)
1920             key_to_remove = (k for k in collision_keys if k in pipfile_dict)
1921             for key in key_to_remove:
1922                 pipfile_dict.pop(key)
1923             pipfile_dict[dict_key] = winning_value
1924         else:
1925             collisions = [key for key in collision_order if key in pipfile_dict.keys()]
1926             if len(collisions) > 1:
1927                 for k in collisions[1:]:
1928                     pipfile_dict.pop(k)
1929         return {name: pipfile_dict}

1955     def __attrs_post_init__(self):
1956         # type: () -> None
1957         if not self.uri:
1958             if self.path:
1959                 self.uri = pip_shims.shims.path_to_url(self.path)
1960         if self.uri is not None:
1961             split = urllib_parse.urlsplit(self.uri)
1962             scheme, rest = split[0], split[1:]
1963             vcs_type = ""
1964             if "+" in scheme:
1965                 vcs_type, scheme = scheme.split("+", 1)
1966                 vcs_type = "{0}+".format(vcs_type)
1967             new_uri = urllib_parse.urlunsplit((scheme,) + rest[:-1] + ("",))
1968             new_uri = "{0}{1}".format(vcs_type, new_uri)
1969             self.uri = new_uri

2039     @req.default
2040     def get_requirement(self):
2041         # type: () -> PackagingRequirement
2042         name = None  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
2043         if self.name:
2044             name = self.name
2045         elif self.link and self.link.egg_fragment:
2046             name = self.link.egg_fragment
2047         url = None
2048         if self.uri:
2049             url = self.uri
2050         elif self.link is not None:
2051             url = self.link.url_without_fragment
2052         if not name:
2053             raise ValueError(
2054                 "pipenv requires an #egg fragment for version controlled "
2055                 "dependencies. Please install remote dependency "
2056                 "in the form {0}#egg=<package-name>.".format(url)
2057             )
2058         req = init_requirement(canonicalize_name(self.name))
2059         req.editable = self.editable
2060         if not getattr(req, "url", None):
2061             if url is not None:

2063             elif self.uri is not None:

2072                 url = url.replace("git+file:/", "git+file:///")
2073             if url:
2074                 req.url = url
2075         line = url if url else self.vcs_uri
2076         if self.editable:
2077             line = "-e {0}".format(line)
2078         req.line = line
2079         if self.ref:
2080             req.revision = self.ref
2081         if self.extras:
2082             req.extras = self.extras
2083         req.vcs = self.vcs
2084         if self.path and self.link and self.link.scheme.startswith("file"):
2085             req.local_file = True
2086             req.path = self.path
2087         req.link = self.link
2088         if (
2089             self.link
2090             and self.link.url_without_fragment
2091             and self.uri
2092             and self.uri != unquote(self.link.url_without_fragment)
2093             and "git+ssh://" in self.link.url
2094             and "git+git@" in self.uri
2095         ):
2096             req.line = self.uri
2097             url = self.link.url_without_fragment
2098             if (
2099                 url
2100                 and url.startswith("git+file:/")
2101                 and not url.startswith("git+file:///")
2102             ):
2103                 url = url.replace("git+file:/", "git+file:///")
2104             req.url = url
2105         return req

2119     def get_checkout_dir(self, src_dir=None):

2136     def get_vcs_repo(self, src_dir=None, checkout_dir=None):

2187     @contextmanager
2188     def locked_vcs_repo(self, src_dir=None):
2189         # type: (Optional[AnyStr]) -> Generator[VCSRepository, None, None]
2190         if not src_dir:
2191             src_dir = create_tracked_tempdir(prefix="requirementslib-", suffix="-src")
2192         vcsrepo = self.get_vcs_repo(src_dir=src_dir)
2193         if not self.req:
2194             if self.parsed_line is not None:
2195                 self.req = self.parsed_line.requirement
2196             else:
2197                 self.req = self.get_requirement()
2198         with pip_shims.shims.global_tempdir_manager():
2199             revision = self.req.revision = vcsrepo.get_commit_hash()
2200 
2201         # Remove potential ref in the end of uri after ref is parsed
2202         if self.link and "@" in self.link.show_url and self.uri and "@" in self.uri:
2203             uri, ref = split_ref_from_uri(self.uri)
2204             checkout = revision
2205             if checkout and ref and ref in checkout:
2206                 self.uri = uri
2207         orig_repo = self._repo
2208         self._repo = vcsrepo
2209         if self._parsed_line:
2210             self._parsed_line.vcsrepo = vcsrepo
2211         if self._setup_info:
2212             self._setup_info = attr.evolve(
2213                 self._setup_info,
2214                 requirements=(),
2215                 _extras_requirements=(),
2216                 build_requires=(),
2217                 setup_requires=(),
2218                 version=None,
2219                 metadata=None,
2220             )
2221         if self.parsed_line and self._parsed_line:
2222             self._parsed_line.vcsrepo = vcsrepo
2223         if self.req and not self.editable:
2224             self.req.specifier = SpecifierSet("=={0}".format(self.setup_info.version))
2225         try:
2226             yield self._repo
2227         except Exception:
2228             self._repo = orig_repo
2229             raise

2231     @classmethod
2232     def from_pipfile(cls, name, pipfile):
2233         # type: (STRING_TYPE, Dict[S, Union[Tuple[S, ...], S, bool]]) -> F
2234         creation_args = {}  # type: Dict[STRING_TYPE, CREATION_ARG_TYPES]
2235         pipfile_keys = [
2236             k
2237             for k in (
2238                 "ref",
2239                 "vcs",
2240                 "subdirectory",
2241                 "path",
2242                 "editable",
2243                 "file",
2244                 "uri",
2245                 "extras",
2246             )
2247             + VCS_LIST
2248             if k in pipfile
2249         ]
2250         # extras = None  # type: Optional[Tuple[STRING_TYPE, ...]]
2251         for key in pipfile_keys:
2252             if key == "extras" and key in pipfile:
2253                 extras = pipfile[key]
2254                 if isinstance(extras, (list, tuple)):
2255                     pipfile[key] = tuple(sorted({extra.lower() for extra in extras}))
2256                 else:
2257                     pipfile[key] = extras
2258             if key in VCS_LIST and key in pipfile_keys:
2259                 creation_args["vcs"] = key
2260                 target = pipfile[key]
2261                 if isinstance(target, six.string_types):
2262                     drive, path = os.path.splitdrive(target)
2263                     if (
2264                         not drive
2265                         and not os.path.exists(target)
2266                         and (
2267                             is_valid_url(target)
2268                             or is_file_url(target)
2269                             or target.startswith("git@")
2270                         )
2271                     ):
2272                         creation_args["uri"] = target
2273                     else:
2274                         creation_args["path"] = target
2275                         if os.path.isabs(target):
2276                             creation_args["uri"] = pip_shims.shims.path_to_url(target)
2277             elif key in pipfile_keys:
2278                 creation_args[key] = pipfile[key]
2279         creation_args["name"] = name
2280         cls_inst = cls(**creation_args)  # type: ignore
2281         return cls_inst
