2289     @property
2290     def line_part(self):
2291         # type: () -> STRING_TYPE
2292         """requirements.txt compatible line part sans-extras."""
2293         base = ""  # type: STRING_TYPE
2294         if self.is_local:
2295             base_link = self.link
2296             if not self.link:
2297                 base_link = self.get_link()
2298             if base_link and base_link.egg_fragment:
2299                 final_format = "{{0}}#egg={0}".format(base_link.egg_fragment)
2300             else:
2301                 final_format = "{0}"
2302             base = final_format.format(self.vcs_uri)
2303         elif self._parsed_line is not None and (
2304             self._parsed_line.is_direct_url and self._parsed_line.line_with_prefix
2305         ):
2306             return self._parsed_line.line_with_prefix
2307         elif getattr(self, "_base_line", None) and (
2308             isinstance(self._base_line, six.string_types)
2309         ):
2310             base = self._base_line
2311         else:
2312             base = getattr(self, "link", self.get_link()).url
2313         if base and self.extras and extras_to_string(self.extras) not in base:
2314             if self.subdirectory:
2315                 base = "{0}".format(self.get_link().url)
2316             else:
2317                 base = "{0}{1}".format(base, extras_to_string(sorted(self.extras)))
2318         if "git+file:/" in base and "git+file:///" not in base:
2319             base = base.replace("git+file:/", "git+file:///")
2320         if self.editable and not base.startswith("-e "):
2321             base = "-e {0}".format(base)
2322         return base

2324     @staticmethod
2325     def _choose_vcs_source(pipfile):
2326         # type: (Dict[S, Union[S, Any]]) -> Dict[S, Union[S, Any]]
2327         src_keys = [k for k in pipfile.keys() if k in ["path", "uri", "file"]]
2328         vcs_type = ""  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
2329         alt_type = ""  # type: Optional[STRING_TYPE]
2330         vcs_value = ""  # type: STRING_TYPE
2331         if src_keys:
2332             chosen_key = next(iter(src_keys))
2333             vcs_type = pipfile.pop("vcs")
2334             if chosen_key in pipfile:
2335                 vcs_value = pipfile[chosen_key]
2336                 alt_type, pipfile_url = split_vcs_method_from_uri(vcs_value)
2337                 if vcs_type is None:
2338                     vcs_type = alt_type
2339             if vcs_type and pipfile_url:
2340                 pipfile[vcs_type] = pipfile_url
2341             for removed in src_keys:
2342                 pipfile.pop(removed)
2343         return pipfile

2345     @property
2346     def pipfile_part(self):
2347         # type: () -> Dict[S, Dict[S, Union[List[S], S, bool, RequirementType, pip_shims.shims.Link]]]
2348         excludes = [
2349             "_repo",
2350             "_base_line",
2351             "setup_path",
2352             "_has_hashed_name",
2353             "pyproject_path",
2354             "pyproject_requires",
2355             "pyproject_backend",
2356             "_setup_info",
2357             "_parsed_line",
2358             "_uri_scheme",
2359         ]
2360         filter_func = lambda k, v: bool(v) is True and k.name not in excludes  # noqa
2361         pipfile_dict = attr.asdict(self, filter=filter_func).copy()
2362         name = pipfile_dict.pop("name", None)
2363         if name is None:
2364             if self.name:
2365                 name = self.name
2366             elif self.parsed_line and self.parsed_line.name:
2367                 name = self.name = self.parsed_line.name
2368             elif self.setup_info and self.setup_info.name:
2369                 name = self.name = self.setup_info.name
2370         if "vcs" in pipfile_dict:
2371             pipfile_dict = self._choose_vcs_source(pipfile_dict)
2372         name, _ = pip_shims.shims._strip_extras(name)
2373         return {name: pipfile_dict}  # type: ignore

2517     def get_line_instance(self):
2518         # type: () -> Line
2519         line_parts = []
2520         if self.req:
2521             if self.req.line_part.startswith("-e "):
2522                 line_parts.extend(self.req.line_part.split(" ", 1))
2523             else:
2524                 line_parts.append(self.req.line_part)
2525         if not self.is_vcs and not self.vcs and self.extras_as_pip:
2526             line_parts.append(self.extras_as_pip)
2527         if self._specifiers and not (self.is_file_or_url or self.is_vcs):
2528             line_parts.append(self._specifiers)
2529         if self.markers:
2530             line_parts.append("; {0}".format(self.markers.replace('"', "'")))
2531         if self.hashes_as_pip and not (self.editable or self.vcs or self.is_vcs):
2532             line_parts.append(self.hashes_as_pip)
2533         if self.editable:
2534             if line_parts[0] == "-e":
2535                 line = "".join(line_parts[1:])
2536             else:
2537                 line = "".join(line_parts)
2538             if self.markers:
2539                 line = '"{0}"'.format(line)
2540             line = "-e {0}".format(line)
2541         else:
2542             line = "".join(line_parts)
2543         return Line(line)

2598         if self._specifiers:

2602             if self.req:

2608                 self.req.req.specifier = specset

2664     @classmethod
2665     @lru_cache()
2666     def from_line(cls, line):
2667         # type: (AnyStr) -> Requirement
2668         if isinstance(line, pip_shims.shims.InstallRequirement):
2669             line = format_requirement(line)
2670         parsed_line = Line(line)
2671         r = (
2672             None
2673         )  # type: Optional[Union[VCSRequirement, FileRequirement, NamedRequirement]]
2674         if (
2675             (parsed_line.is_file and parsed_line.is_installable)
2676             or parsed_line.is_remote_url
2677         ) and not parsed_line.is_vcs:
2678             r = file_req_from_parsed_line(parsed_line)
2679         elif parsed_line.is_vcs:
2680             r = vcs_req_from_parsed_line(parsed_line)
2681         elif line == "." and not is_installable_file(line):
2682             raise RequirementError(
2683                 "Error parsing requirement %s -- are you sure it is installable?" % line
2684             )
2685         else:
2686             r = named_req_from_parsed_line(parsed_line)
2687         req_markers = None
2688         if parsed_line.markers:
2689             req_markers = PackagingRequirement("fakepkg; {0}".format(parsed_line.markers))
2690         if r is not None and r.req is not None:
2691             r.req.marker = getattr(req_markers, "marker", None) if req_markers else None
2692         args = {}  # type: Dict[STRING_TYPE, CREATION_ARG_TYPES]
2693         args = {
2694             "name": r.name,
2695             "vcs": parsed_line.vcs,
2696             "req": r,
2697             "markers": parsed_line.markers,
2698             "editable": parsed_line.editable,
2699             "line_instance": parsed_line,
2700         }
2701         if parsed_line.extras:
2702             extras = ()  # type: Tuple[STRING_TYPE, ...]
2703             extras = tuple(sorted(dedup([extra.lower() for extra in parsed_line.extras])))
2704             args["extras"] = extras
2705             if r is not None:
2706                 r.extras = extras
2707             elif r is not None and r.extras is not None:
2708                 args["extras"] = tuple(
2709                     sorted(dedup([extra.lower() for extra in r.extras]))
2710                 )  # type: ignore
2711             if r.req is not None:
2712                 r.req.extras = args["extras"]
2713         if parsed_line.hashes:
2714             args["hashes"] = tuple(parsed_line.hashes)  # type: ignore
2715         cls_inst = cls(**args)  # type: ignore
2716         return cls_inst

2728     @classmethod
2729     def from_pipfile(cls, name, pipfile):
2730         from .markers import PipenvMarkers
2731 
2732         _pipfile = {}
2733         if hasattr(pipfile, "keys"):
2734             _pipfile = dict(pipfile).copy()
2735         _pipfile["version"] = get_version(pipfile)
2736         vcs = next(iter([vcs for vcs in VCS_LIST if vcs in _pipfile]), None)
2737         if vcs:
2738             _pipfile["vcs"] = vcs
2739             r = VCSRequirement.from_pipfile(name, pipfile)
2740         elif any(key in _pipfile for key in ["path", "file", "uri"]):
2741             r = FileRequirement.from_pipfile(name, pipfile)
2742         else:
2743             r = NamedRequirement.from_pipfile(name, pipfile)
2744         markers = PipenvMarkers.from_pipfile(name, _pipfile)
2745         req_markers = None
2746         if markers:
2747             markers = str(markers)
2748             req_markers = PackagingRequirement("fakepkg; {0}".format(markers))
2749             if r.req is not None:
2750                 r.req.marker = req_markers.marker
2751         extras = _pipfile.get("extras")
2752         if r.req:
2753             if r.req.specifier:
2754                 r.req.specifier = SpecifierSet(_pipfile["version"])
2755             r.req.extras = (
2756                 tuple(sorted(dedup([extra.lower() for extra in extras])))
2757                 if extras
2758                 else ()
2759             )
2760         args = {
2761             "name": r.name,
2762             "vcs": vcs,
2763             "req": r,
2764             "markers": markers,
2765             "extras": tuple(_pipfile.get("extras", ())),
2766             "editable": _pipfile.get("editable", False),
2767             "index": _pipfile.get("index"),
2768         }
2769         if any(key in _pipfile for key in ["hash", "hashes"]):
2770             args["hashes"] = _pipfile.get("hashes", [pipfile.get("hash")])
2771         cls_inst = cls(**args)
2772         return cls_inst

2774     def as_line(
2775         self,
2776         sources=None,
2777         include_hashes=True,
2778         include_extras=True,
2779         include_markers=True,
2780         as_list=False,
2781     ):
2782         """Format this requirement as a line in requirements.txt.
2783 
2784         If ``sources`` provided, it should be an sequence of mappings, containing
2785         all possible sources to be used for this requirement.
2786 
2787         If ``sources`` is omitted or falsy, no index information will be included
2788         in the requirement line.
2789         """
2790 
2791         assert self.line_instance is not None
2792         parts = self.line_instance.get_line(
2793             with_prefix=True,
2794             with_hashes=include_hashes,
2795             with_markers=include_markers,
2796             as_list=as_list,
2797         )
2798         if sources and self.requirement and not (self.line_instance.is_local or self.vcs):
2799             from ..utils import prepare_pip_source_args
2800 
2801             if self.index:
2802                 sources = [s for s in sources if s.get("name") == self.index]
2803             source_list = prepare_pip_source_args(sources)
2804             if as_list:
2805                 parts.extend(sources)
2806             else:
2807                 index_string = " ".join(source_list)
2808                 parts = "{0} {1}".format(parts, index_string)
2809         return parts
2810 
2811     def get_markers(self):
2812         # type: () -> Marker
2813         markers = self.markers
2814         if markers:
2815             fake_pkg = PackagingRequirement("fakepkg; {0}".format(markers))
2816             markers = fake_pkg.marker
2817         return markers

2829     def get_requirement(self):
2830         req_line = self.req.req.line
2831         if req_line.startswith("-e "):
2832             _, req_line = req_line.split(" ", 1)
2833         req = init_requirement(self.name)
2834         req.line = req_line
2835         req.specifier = SpecifierSet(self.specifiers if self.specifiers else "")
2836         if self.is_vcs or self.is_file_or_url:
2837             req.url = getattr(self.req.req, "url", self.req.link.url_without_fragment)
2838         req.marker = self.get_markers()
2839         req.extras = set(self.extras) if self.extras else set()
2840         return req

2854     def as_pipfile(self):
2855         good_keys = (
2856             "hashes",
2857             "extras",
2858             "markers",
2859             "editable",
2860             "version",
2861             "index",
2862         ) + VCS_LIST
2863         req_dict = {
2864             k: v
2865             for k, v in attr.asdict(self, recurse=False, filter=filter_none).items()
2866             if k in good_keys
2867         }
2868         name = self.name
2869         if "markers" in req_dict and req_dict["markers"]:
2870             req_dict["markers"] = req_dict["markers"].replace('"', "'")
2871         if not self.req.name:
2872             name_carriers = (self.req, self, self.line_instance, self.req.parsed_line)
2873             name_options = [
2874                 getattr(carrier, "name", None)
2875                 for carrier in name_carriers
2876                 if carrier is not None
2877             ]
2878             req_name = next(iter(n for n in name_options if n is not None), None)
2879             self.req.name = req_name
2880         req_name, dict_from_subreq = self.req.pipfile_part.popitem()
2881         base_dict = {
2882             k: v
2883             for k, v in dict_from_subreq.items()
2884             if k not in ["req", "link", "_setup_info"]
2885         }
2886         base_dict.update(req_dict)
2887         conflicting_keys = ("file", "path", "uri")
2888         if "file" in base_dict and any(k in base_dict for k in conflicting_keys[1:]):
2889             conflicts = [k for k in (conflicting_keys[1:],) if k in base_dict]
2890             for k in conflicts:
2891                 base_dict.pop(k)
2892         if "hashes" in base_dict:
2893             _hashes = base_dict.pop("hashes")
2894             hashes = []
2895             for _hash in _hashes:
2896                 try:
2897                     hashes.append(_hash.as_line())
2898                 except AttributeError:
2899                     hashes.append(_hash)
2900             base_dict["hashes"] = sorted(hashes)
2901         if "extras" in base_dict:
2902             base_dict["extras"] = list(base_dict["extras"])
2903         if len(base_dict.keys()) == 1 and "version" in base_dict:
2904             base_dict = base_dict.get("version")
2905         return {name: base_dict}
2906 
2907     def as_ireq(self):
2908         if self.line_instance and self.line_instance.ireq:
2909             return self.line_instance.ireq
2910         elif getattr(self.req, "_parsed_line", None) and self.req._parsed_line.ireq:
2911             return self.req._parsed_line.ireq
2912         kwargs = {"include_hashes": False}
2913         if (self.is_file_or_url and self.req.is_local) or self.is_vcs:
2914             kwargs["include_markers"] = False
2915         ireq_line = self.as_line(**kwargs)
2916         ireq = Line(ireq_line).ireq
2917         if not getattr(ireq, "req", None):
2918             ireq.req = self.req.req
2919             if (self.is_file_or_url and self.req.is_local) or self.is_vcs:
2920                 if getattr(ireq, "req", None) and getattr(ireq.req, "marker", None):
2921                     ireq.req.marker = None
2922         else:
2923             ireq.req.extras = self.req.req.extras
2924             if not ((self.is_file_or_url and self.req.is_local) or self.is_vcs):
2925                 ireq.req.marker = self.req.req.marker
2926         return ireq
2927

2936     def get_dependencies(self, sources=None):
2937         """Retrieve the dependencies of the current requirement.
2938 
2939         Retrieves dependencies of the current requirement.  This only works on pinned
2940         requirements.
2941 
2942         :param sources: Pipfile-formatted sources, defaults to None
2943         :param sources: list[dict], optional
2944         :return: A set of requirement strings of the dependencies of this requirement.
2945         :rtype: set(str)
2946         """
2947 
2948         from .dependencies import get_dependencies
2949 
2950         if not sources:
2951             sources = [
2952                 {"name": "pypi", "url": "https://pypi.org/simple", "verify_ssl": True}
2953             ]
2954         return get_dependencies(self.as_ireq(), sources=sources)

2956     def get_abstract_dependencies(self, sources=None):
2957         """Retrieve the abstract dependencies of this requirement.
2958 
2959         Returns the abstract dependencies of the current requirement in order to resolve.
2960 
2961         :param sources: A list of sources (pipfile format), defaults to None
2962         :param sources: list, optional
2963         :return: A list of abstract (unpinned) dependencies
2964         :rtype: list[ :class:`~requirementslib.models.dependency.AbstractDependency` ]
2965         """
2966 
2967         from .dependencies import (
2968             AbstractDependency,
2969             get_dependencies,
2970             get_abstract_dependencies,
2971         )
2972 
2973         if not self.abstract_dep:
2974             parent = getattr(self, "parent", None)
2975             self.abstract_dep = AbstractDependency.from_requirement(self, parent=parent)
2976         if not sources:
2977             sources = [
2978                 {"url": "https://pypi.org/simple", "name": "pypi", "verify_ssl": True}
2979             ]
2980         if is_pinned_requirement(self.ireq):
2981             deps = self.get_dependencies()
2982         else:
2983             ireq = sorted(self.find_all_matches(), key=lambda k: k.version)
2984             deps = get_dependencies(ireq.pop(), sources=sources)
2985         return get_abstract_dependencies(deps, sources=sources, parent=self.abstract_dep)

3006     def run_requires(self, sources=None, finder=None):
3007         if self.req and self.req.setup_info is not None:
3008             info_dict = self.req.setup_info.as_dict()
3009         elif self.line_instance and self.line_instance.setup_info is not None:
3010             info_dict = self.line_instance.setup_info.as_dict()
3011         else:
3012 
3013             if not finder:
3014                 from .dependencies import get_finder
3015 
3016                 finder = get_finder(sources=sources)
3017             with pip_shims.shims.global_tempdir_manager():
3018                 info = SetupInfo.from_requirement(self, finder=finder)
3019                 if info is None:
3020                     return {}
3021                 info_dict = info.get_info()
3022             if self.req and not self.req.setup_info:
3023                 self.req._setup_info = info
3024         if self.req._has_hashed_name and info_dict.get("name"):
3025             self.req.name = self.name = info_dict["name"]
3026             if self.req.req.name != info_dict["name"]:
3027                 self.req.req.name = info_dict["name"]
3028         return info_dict

3030     def merge_markers(self, markers):
3031         # type: (Union[AnyStr, Marker]) -> None
3032         if not markers:
3033             return self
3034         if not isinstance(markers, Marker):
3035             markers = Marker(markers)
3036         _markers = []  # type: List[Marker]
3037         ireq = self.as_ireq()
3038         if ireq and ireq.markers:
3039             ireq_marker = ireq.markers
3040             _markers.append(str(ireq_marker))
3041         _markers.append(str(markers))
3042         marker_str = " and ".join([normalize_marker_str(m) for m in _markers if m])
3043         new_marker = Marker(marker_str)
3044         line = copy.deepcopy(self._line_instance)
3045         line.markers = marker_str
3046         line.parsed_marker = new_marker
3047         if getattr(line, "_requirement", None) is not None:
3048             line._requirement.marker = new_marker
3049         if getattr(line, "_ireq", None) is not None and line._ireq.req:
3050             line._ireq.req.marker = new_marker
3051         new_ireq = getattr(self, "ireq", None)
3052         if new_ireq and new_ireq.req:
3053             new_ireq.req.marker = new_marker
3054         req = self.req
3055         if req.req:
3056             req_requirement = req.req
3057             req_requirement.marker = new_marker
3058             req = attr.evolve(req, req=req_requirement, parsed_line=line)
3059         return attr.evolve(
3060             self, markers=str(new_marker), ireq=new_ireq, req=req, line_instance=line
3061         )
